headline: Caterpillar, Honeywell, and Chevron Lead the Dow Jones in 2026
summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average (NYSEARCA:DIA) has climbed 3.4% year-to-date through Wednesday, but three industrial and energy giants are leaving the broader index behind. Caterpillar (NYSE:CAT), Honeywell (NASDAQ:HON), and Chevron (NYSE:CVX) are leading the Dow’s 2026 charge with double-digit gains driven by record earnings, strategic restructuring, and energy market resilience.
